  "prompt": "Does the law differentiate between intentional and unintentional money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, the law typically distinguishes between intentional and unintentional money laundering. Intentional money laundering involves knowingly conducting financial transactions with illegally obtained funds, while unintentional money laundering might occur through negligence or lack of awareness. The legal consequences and penalties can vary significantly based on the intent and circumstances.\n\nIntentional money laundering generally carries more severe criminal penalties, including:\n- Higher potential prison sentences\n- Larger financial penalties\n- More serious criminal charges\n\nUnintentional money laundering might result in:\n- Civil penalties\n- Compliance requirements\n- Mandatory training\n- Potential fines\n- Less severe legal consequences\n\nThe specific distinctions and consequences depend on the jurisdiction and specific legal framework. Financial institutions and professionals are typically required to have robust compliance programs to prevent unintentional money laundering.",
